args: Orsem called me to the courtyard,\nbut I'm not entirely sure why.
That guy got you out here too,\n{player_name}?
I'm assuming we both received the same\ninvitation.
Oh, it's not just the two of you.
What in the world could he be planning?
Ah, wonderful! You all made it.
Because I'm going to teach you more\nabout the magic of skating!
And on that note...ta-daaah! Let our deep\ndive into the art of the foot blades begin!
If I'm not mistaken, skating involves\ngliding atop frozen surfaces, yes?
I fear we have no such areas here in\nthe courtyard.
Aw, don't worry your head over that!\nTake a gander here. If I do like so...
He's stickin' somethin' to his shoes.
These are my skating blades. If I slip them\non my shoes like so and stand...
Holy cow! The spot under your feet just\nturned to ice!
Right you are! When you attach these\nblades to your shoes, you can create a\npath of ice anywhere you like.
So, when we first saw you running on the\nriver, it's because you were using these\nmagic shoes to freeze it?
Magic BLADES, my good man. Not shoes.\nBut yes, they are imbued with ice mana.
The place I come from is a snowy land,\nand all of my people are deft hands when\nit comes to wielding ice mana.
And with these ice-infused blades,\na person can skate in all sorts of places?
Exactly so! That's why skating is super\nduper MEGA popular where I come from!\n...Or it used to be.
Er, well, you see... That is, I... Um...
M-more importantly, I'd love for all of you\nto try skating! It's SO much fun!
Yeah, but don't we need yer magic shoe\ndealies?
Magic BLADES! Not shoes. Goodness me.\nBut here, why don't you just take these\nand give 'em a whirl?!
How many'a these things do ya have?!
Crateloads! I won't rest until every person\nin the world knows the magic of gracefully\ngliding across the ice.
I never go anywhere without spare blades.\nYou never know when there might be\nsomeone else ready to be converted!
This seems like an incredible amount of\neffort merely to spread word of a hobby.
A hobby that is, alas, little known outside\nof my people.
Which is why it's my duty to spread the\ngood word to all.
I suppose I hadn't even heard of it before\nmeeting you.
Exactly! And there are loads of people just\nlike you!
Doesn't it seem like a waste that\nsomething so enjoyable isn't better\nknown among the people?
Hence, this is now my life's work.
Let me make sure I understand: You left\nyour hometown and now travel the world\nall alone so you can talk about...skating?
Bwa ha ha! It's like yer some kinda public\nambassador or missionary or whatever!
I do hope that you all come to love skating\nas much as I.
And I'll do anything to make it happen!
Wanna give it a shot? I'm happy to show\nyou all my techniques!
Well, we can't very well refuse after such\na...passionate display.
Yaaay! Then let's get to it!
First, attach the blades to your shoes and\nstand on the ground.
Then you go like ＂hngh!＂ and push\nforward like ＂yaaah!＂ and skate along the\nice like ＂fsssheeeewww!＂
And THEN you do like ＂boing!＂ and a\nflip. Oh, and when you stop, you do a spin\nlike ＂bwwaaawawawawawa!＂
Your attitude is commendable, but your\ninstructional technique...needs much work.
